## Animations & Interactions

Keep animations minimal and purposeful:

```css
/* Price flash on update */
@keyframes priceFlash {
  0% { color: var(--gold2); }
  50% { color: var(--green); background: rgba(46,204,113,0.1); }
  100% { color: var(--gold2); }
}

/* Status dot pulse */
@keyframes pulse {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
  50% { opacity: 0.4; }
}

/* Panel entry */
@keyframes fadeIn {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(4px); }
  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
```

**Rules:**

- Flash gold price briefly when it updates from WebSocket
- Pulse green dot on active status indicators
- Subtle fadeIn on panel mount (animation-delay stagger: 50ms per panel)
- NO page transition animations — instant page switches only
- NO loading spinners except on AI-generating states (use a pulsing dot)

---

## Responsive Behavior

- **Desktop (>1200px):** Full layout as specified above
- **Tablet (900–1200px):** Collapse 3-column grids to 2-column
- **Mobile (<900px):**
  - Sidebar collapses to bottom tab bar (5 icons max)
  - Single column layout
  - Top bar shows price + time only
  - All panels stack vertically
  - Prioritize: Questions frame → Price → Levels → News → Calendar

Mobile is primarily used for reading alerts. Keep it readable and fast.

