## Formatting Utilities

Always use these formatters — never inline formatting logic:

```javascript
// lib/formatters.js

export const formatPrice = (price) =>
  new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 }).format(price);
// → "2,348.20"

export const formatChange = (change, pct) => {
  const sign = change >= 0 ? '+' : '';
  return `${sign}${formatPrice(change)} (${sign}${pct.toFixed(2)}%)`;
};
// → "+14.10 (+0.60%)"

export const formatWAT = (date) =>
  new Date(date).toLocaleTimeString('en-US', { timeZone: 'Africa/Lagos', hour12: false });
// → "08:41:22"

export const formatRR = (rr) => `1:${Math.abs(rr).toFixed(1)}`;
// → "1:2.1"
```

---

## What Never to Do

- Never use Inter, Roboto, or system fonts
- Never use purple, violet, or gradient backgrounds
- Never use rounded corners larger than 6px on panels
- Never use box-shadow for decoration (only for glows on active elements)
- Never use heavy page transition animations
- Never show loading spinners (use skeleton loaders or pulsing dots)
- Never show raw API error objects to the user
- Never let a failed AI call crash a panel — always show fallback content
- Never use a chart library (Recharts, Chart.js etc.) for the sparklines or bar charts — build them with SVG or CSS
- Never use Tailwind utility classes for typography — define all type styles in globals.css using the IBM Plex fonts
- Never make the sidebar wider than 52px on desktop
- Never add padding larger than 16px inside panels

